FBIS3-45913 "drchi016_w_94008" FBIS-CHI-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 HONG KONG & MACAO Macao Macao Group Campaigns To Popularize Basic Law OW2301155594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1459 GMT 23 Jan 94 OW2301155594 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Macao, January 23 (XINHUA) -- A drive aiming to popularize the Basic Law of the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) among local residents was launched here today. Sponsored by the Association for Promoting the Basic Law of Macao SAR, today's activity includes an exhibition which through pictures and short articles introduced the content and significance of the Macao Basic Law to local residents and visitors. An organizer of the activity said the Basic Law, a constitutional document of the future Macao SAR, is closely linked with the interest of local people. It is an urgent task in the remaining years of the transitional period to introduce the Basic Law to local residents, especially youths and children. He said that more activities of this kind will be held this year for the purpose to make local people learn more about and be more concerned with the Basic Law. Guo Dongpo, director of the XINHUA news agency Macao branch, Ke Zhengping, advisor to the branch and some noted personages in Macao including Ma Man Ke and Ho Hau Wah attended today's activity.
